Package it.polimi.ingsw.PSP38.common

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BytesForBoard
    Class made of a series of unmodifiable byte parameters that represent the different status of a cell of the board
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Message
    Enumeration class that contains all the possible messages that the server is able to send to the clients connected to it
    Protocol
    Enumeration which represents the type of messages that can be sent by the server to the clients:
    -NOTIFY_MESSAGE is used if the server needs to send to one or more client a notification message (e. g. if someone has won the game)
    -ASK_INT is used if the server needs to use an integer defined by the user through the client
    -ASK_STRING is used if the server needs to use a string defined by the user through the client
    -DISPLAY_BOARD is used when the server asks the client to show the game board to the user
    WorkerColor
    Different colors that a worker can have (WHITE, BLACK, BLUE).
